1: No, it is not alive, nor does it derive "sustenance" from anyone ensnared. It does not expresses any form of will or consciousnesses in any way. Any "intelligence" attributed to it are most likely the result of the human brain anthropomorphizing inanimate objects, such as seeing a "face" on the front of the car, or attributing "moods" to a computer's performance.

All tests have shown that items are composed of common metals, with few exceptions, but no super-rare or unidentified metals. Scanning and probing have show no differentiation in construction, showing the mass to be sharp and/or pointed objects throughout.

2: As of yet, items removed from SCP-162 do not appear to carry over it's unique properties. Items removed from SCP-162 function normally, with no abnormal affects observed.

Items do not "grow" when attached or removed from SCP-162. The only way to increase the size of SCP-162 is to add additional items.

Cross-testing with SCP-914 has been postponed, with concerns raised about SCP-162 possibly connecting to and "infesting" SCP-914.







